# 
AI Agents for
Video Editing 
A new paradigm for video editing. Accelerate hours of editing work to seconds with AI agents.
Early Access

## Tiles
Tile by tile, craft your Mosaic. Each tile represents a video editing operation and is configurable, so you can guide outputs.Tiles strung together define an Agent's editing flow.

## Canvas
Drag and drop Tiles in a visual canvas to automate your editing workflow. Use pre-built templates or start from scratch.Branch and create multiple variants from one video. Run in parallel and watch how your content evolves through each step of the Agent's editing flow.
![Canvas](https://usemosaic.ai/_next/image?url=%2Ffeature_canvas.png&w=3840&q=100)
![Flow State Visualization](https://usemosaic.ai/_next/image?url=%2Fflow.png&w=3840&q=100)
![1 Video → 10 Videos](https://usemosaic.ai/_next/image?url=%2Ffeature_canvas_variants.png&w=3840&q=100)
### 1 Video → 10 Videos
Generate different versions of your video simultaneously.
![Run in Parallel](https://usemosaic.ai/_next/image?url=%2Ffeature_canvas_parallel.png&w=3840&q=100)
### Run in Parallel
Run branches in parallel. Run agents in parallel.
![Instant Preview](https://usemosaic.ai/_next/image?url=%2Ffeature_canvas_preview.png&w=3840&q=100)
### Instant Preview
Track and see results directly in the Canvas.
![Jump to Editor](https://usemosaic.ai/_next/image?url=%2Ffeature_canvas_edit.png&w=3840&q=100)
### Jump to Editor
Jump into Editor from any step. Tweak and polish with Chat.
## Agents
An Agent is a sequence of Tiles configured for specific editing use cases. Templates are pre-buillt Agents that can be ran as is or forked as a starting point.During runtime, Agents make their own evaluation and optimization decisions to ensure good results.

## Chat
Chat lets you talk with a multimodal AI and edit your videos in natural language. Chat understands your video, so you can ask it to perform edits based on what it sees and hears.

generated_description:
**Mosaic: Revolutionizing Video Editing with AI**

Mosaic is a fresh startup that burst onto the scene in 2024, based in San Francisco. Its mission? To create AI agents that make video editing a breeze, turning hours of work into just seconds. Imagine being able to build your own tailored video editing agents on a visually intuitive, node-based canvas. That's Mosaic's game plan.

Initially conceived as an "agentic video editing paradigm," Mosaic empowers users to drag and drop 'Tiles'—simple video editing operations within a customizable structure. These Tiles can be strung together, forming 'Agents' that automate the editing process tailored to specific needs. Whether you want to trim a video, add captions, or enhance audio, Mosaic's AI has got you covered, allowing you to generate multiple video versions simultaneously.

Currently in early access, Mosaic is part of Y Combinator's Batch W25, where it’s been gaining traction and support from notable industry players, including Harj Taggar as their group partner. With a team of just two, they're pushing hard for innovation in video editing with features like a visual 'Canvas' for workflow automation, live editing via 'Chat', and an array of use cases catering to different content needs.

Mosaic's capabilities are already being proven—securing first place in the Google Gemini Competition is a testament to the potential they hold. If you're interested, they invite you to join their Discord community and participate in shaping the future of video editing.

For the latest details and possible early access, check their [website](https://usemosaic.ai). In a world where video content is king, Mosaic could very well be the secret weapon creators have been waiting for. Keep your eyes on them.
